<br>
There's a couple good discussions in general about aa's on the first 2-3 pages worth looking through.  If you're not a member yet, you might want to sign up (free membership).  Lots of good info here.  Only downside is a lot of posters are lvl 65 (or close) raiding clerics with lots of aa's.  A minority are casual players or from not Ssra/VT/PoP guilds.<br>
<br>
But, it really depends on your style.  The general consensus seems to be get run 3 (even if you have jboots) and then don't do any aa until lvl 65 (that 2nd part from the raiding guild folks who have access to content in tier 2+ zones; without that stay at lvl 60 and aa until you can as it's easier to find more mobs that give you exp at 60 than 62 or 65).  Others suggest if your mana is low and you're poor, try getting SCM maxxed so you can save on heals and stuff.<br>
<br>
Lots of paths to follow.  I was an exception; started aa's at lvl 54 with 10% going to aa (figured 54 was a hell level so I'd never miss a bit more exp).  I kept it 10-20% at all times.  When I hit lvl 60, I had 8 aa's.  Now at lvl 62, I have 47 aa's so far because I got flagged for tier 2 and that is where all but 1-2 of the aa's came from.<br>
<br>
Not a full answer, but there's a lot of good information out there for you.<br>
<br>
