<br>
This should help give you some perspectives. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crystilla>crystilla</A> at: 4/1/03 3:33:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morinkhanmt>MorinkhanMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 307<br> <font color=#628CBC>(4/1/03 10:12:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA</span><hr size=1> Do what feels right for yourself, depending on what a typical EQ night contains.<br>
<br>
If your playstyle leans towards raiding, levels are generally more important than AAs... you get more mana and hp, you get better resists, you get better spells.<br>
<br>
If you're more casual, maybe putting a small percentage of your xp towards AAs at an earlier level makes sense.<br>
<br>
Most of the AAs for a cleric aren't available until higher levels anyway. At 53, you can start on your general skills, such as Run3, but your the most useful AAs for a cleric (Spell Casting Mastery, Divine Arbitration, Healing Adept/Gift, etc) aren't available until you hit higher levels anyway.<br>
<br>
If you're working at levelling to 65 and getting lots of AA abilities, I'd recommend getting to L60 before dedicating much of your xp to AAs. At 60, you have a wider variety of more useful skills to choose from.<br>
<br>
As Crys said, there are several threads of info and recommendations on AA paths on the EQCleric boards. Ultimately, it depends on you. Stuff like Run3 is nice to have at any level, but in my opinion, getting more levels and better spells is a much faster and stronger way of increasing your character's strength. Most AAs are simply enhancements, while levels and spells are the real strength of your cleric.<br>
<br>
Good luck =) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47567">Morinkhan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.furysedge.com">Fury's Edge</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Morell Thule</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=niphreedil>Niphreedil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#628CBC>(4/4/03 11:14:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://membres.lycos.fr/niphreedil/niphreedil.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA</span><hr size=1> If you're going to level to 60 to get your AAs, I'd suggest to go to 61 instead, for the following reasons:<br>
<br>
1. At 60 each death is a big xp drain, seeing you loose a full yellow is no fun.<br>
<br>
2. At 61 you have access to planar AAs. Divine Arbitration and Radiant Cure come to mind, very useful tricks even at rank 1.<br>
<br>
3. I've found that, spell-wise, 56 &gt;&gt;&gt; 55 and 61 &gt;&gt;&gt; 60.<br>
<br>
4. You can buy all your 61 spells in the Bazaar at low price now.<br>
<br>
The drawback is that you must love PoP. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Also, you'll eventually be tempted to get flagged, resulting in a lot of wasted time that could have been used to grind AA xp. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
